{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"51259b89-4ba0-404a-a5a1-3b70399526f7","content":"Two things change with MTP:\n\n### 1. `--filter` → `--treenode-filter` (passed after `--`)\n\nMTP replaces the VSTest filter engine with a **tree-node filter**. The syntax changes from property expressions to a path/property hybrid:\n\n| Concept | Old (VSTest) | New (MTP treenode) |\n|---|---|---|\n| Name contains | `FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests` | `/**/*IntegrationTests*` |\n| Trait match | `Category=Smoke` | `[Category=Smoke]` |\n| AND | `&` | combine path + `[]` |\n\n### 2. Your translated command\n\n```bash\ndotnet test -- --treenode-filter \"/**/*IntegrationTests*[Category=Smoke]\"\n```\n\n- `/**/` — match any namespace/class depth  \n- `*IntegrationTests*` — name contains \"IntegrationTests\"  \n- `[Category=Smoke]` — trait property filter (xUnit v3 exposes `[Trait(\"Category\",\"Smoke\")]` as a node property)\n\n### Running directly as an executable (MTP also supports this)\n\nSince `UseMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner=true` makes the test project an executable:\n\n```bash\ndotnet run --project TestProject.csproj -- --treenode-filter \"/**/*IntegrationTests*[Category=Smoke]\"\n```\n\n### Quick reference for operators\n\n```\n/Foo/Bar       exact path\n/**/Bar        Bar at any depth\n/Foo/*         all children of Foo\n[Key=Value]    property equals\n[Key~=Sub]     property contains (if supported)\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"36317008-5dc6-43f8-b794-97213a17c0d8","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is migrating from xUnit v2 to xUnit v3 with MTP (Microsoft Testing Platform). The key changes are:\n\n1. With MTP (`UseMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner=true`), the test executable becomes its own test runner\n2. The `--filter` syntax from VSTest (`dotnet test --filter`) changes when using MTP\n3. In MTP, the filter is passed via `--treenode-filter` instead of `--filter`\n\nLet me explain the differences:\n\n**Old (VSTest with xUnit v2):**\n```\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n\n\n```\n\n**New (MTP with xUnit v3):**\nWith MTP, the filter syntax transforms—`FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests` becomes a path-based filter like `/IntegrationTests/`, and trait filters like `Category=Smoke` are wrapped in brackets as `[Category=Smoke]`. The command structure changes to use `--treenode-filter` instead of `--filter`, though `dotnet test` still works as the entry point.\n\nMTP's tree-based filtering supports path matching with wildcards (`/**/*IntegrationTests*/**`), property matching with bracket notation (`[Trait.Category=Smoke]`), and combinations of both. The key shift is moving from VSTest's property-based filters to MTP's hierarchical node syntax.\n\n```\n/MyApp.Tests/IntegrationTests[Category=Smoke]\n```\n\nor more generally:\n```\n/**/*IntegrationTests*/**[Category=Smoke]\n```\n\nActually, let me reconsider the proper MTP treenode filter syntax. The path-like structure uses `/` to separate levels, `*` for single-level wildcards, `**` for multi-level wildcards, and `[property=value]` for property filtering. Since xUnit v3 maps traits as properties on test nodes, I can translate the old filter syntax to the new treenode format using `--treenode-filter`, or stick with `--filter` and let MTP bridge the syntax.\n\nThe key difference is that with MTP, traits might be exposed differently—possibly as `trait.Category` rather than just `Category`—so the compatibility layer might not recognize the old trait syntax directly. The safer approach is to use the native MTP treenode filter syntax instead of relying on the VSTest bridge. The key distinction is that `--treenode-filter` uses a path-based syntax with property filters in brackets like `[trait.Category=Smoke]`, while the traditional `--filter` approach needs adjusted property names. I'm weighing which approach makes more sense for the user's scenario—the native MTP syntax versus keeping the familiar filter format with the right property naming conventions.","outputTokens":2128,"requestId":"E82A:11815A:26CD81A:29497AA:6A049433"},"id":"05e23d4b-708c-4ddb-a059-3193b9a1faff","timestamp":"2026-05-13T15:10:21.232Z","parentId":"3e68e44d-10da-4f75-8b21-f177d3fab1c1"}
